Eze Bright Sunday aka Heartless has released his debut Elongated Play entitled Unforeseen. The vocalist releases his debut EP “Unforeseen” via his indie company Heartless Records after taking some time to hone his skills. The 17-minute project features six tracks and provides a brief look inside the artist’s universe. Idahams, Bhadboy Silver, and Mosidon make cameo appearances as well.   Omah Lay expresses fulfillment after December event     Yaba Buluku Boyz makes impact on Nigeria music scene     Sotayogaga preaches peace after new role as Queen Mother   Read Also: Omah Lay expresses fulfillment after December event Heartless is a Nigerian musician and songwriter who is establishing himself as a force to be reckoned with in the country’s music business. - Advertisement - Heartless is an Afrobeats artist who was born and raised in Port Harcourt, River State. His music is delivered in a mashup of Igbo and English. His first taste of fame came in 2020, when he released his track “Too Much,” which featured popular Nigerian and fellow Port Harcourt native Idahams.